This paper is about using simulation to improve semantic segmentation in self-driving scenes. The paper focuses on domain generalization, which is a common problem in computer vision and machine learning. Given that the paper is about computer vision and machine learning, it is likely to belong to the cs.CV sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach to learning domain-invariant representations, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.LG sub-category. The paper also uses auxiliary datasets to improve the generalizability of the model, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.AI sub-category. Finally, the paper is about self-driving scenes, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.RO sub-category. There is also a focus on security and privacy, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.CR sub-category.
